subSubSection.paragraph:
Thorax.
Posterior and anterior margin of pronotum forming a tight narrowing in the centre. Hind wing pads absent. Forefemur (
Fig. 7
): Length about 4.5x maximum width; dorsally with a row of long, fine and simple setae alternating with 8 –11 clavate setae, length 0.2 width of femur; ventrally with micropores; short, fine, simple setae and one row of spine-like setae. Coxal gills absent. Tibia: 1.1x length of femur, dorsally with one row long, fine, simple setae, ventrally with one row of short, fine, simple spine-like setae. Tarsus: 2.6x shorter than the tibia. Dorsally with short, fine, simple setae; ventrally with one row of short spine-like setae; tarsal claw (
Fig. 9
) with one row of 9–10 denticles increasing in size distally.

Distribution. Peru , Lima Region , Chillon River Basin (Domínguez et al. 2012;
Mayo 1972
).
